# Solrmarc::Wrapper

Ruby wrapper for accessing SolrMarc methods

## Installation

Add this line to your application's Gemfile:

    gem 'solrmarc-wrapper'

And then execute:

    $ bundle

Or install it yourself as:

    $ gem install solrmarc-wrapper

## Usage

This gem must be run under JRuby, and also requires a solrmarc dist directory and solr url (see config/settings.yml)

Example:  this retrieves the full marc record stored in the Solr index, runs it through SolrMarc indexing to get a SolrInputDocument from the marcxml
It identifies Solr documents by the Solr "id" field, and expects the marc to be stored in a Solr field "marcxml"
If there is no single document matching the id, an error is logged and nil is returned

def solr_input_doc(id)
   @solrmarc_wrapper.get_solr_input_doc_from_marcxml(id)
end


